title: USGS National Geospatial Program Data Acquisition Plans
name: usgs-national-geospatial-program-data-acquisition-plans
notes: U.S. Geological Survey, Department of the Interior  -  Data Acquisition Plans for the National Geospatial Program.  This harvest source serves as the repository for NGP Planned Acquisitions to populate the Geospatial Platform 'MarketPlace'.  Published Acquisition Plans will primarily be for our A-16 and National Geospatial Data Assets (NGDAs) responsibilities to include:  Elevation, Hydrography, Geographic Names, and Land Use/Land Cover.

organization.description:
http://www.usgs.gov/
The USGS is a federal science agency that provides impartial information on the health of our ecosystems and environment, the natural hazards that threaten us, the natural resources we rely on, the impacts of climate and land-use change, and the core science systems that help us provide timely, relevant, and useable information.
